'''Anyaa Sowutuom''' is a constituency represented in the [[Parliament of Ghana]]. It elects one [[Member of Parliament|Member of Parliament (MP)]] by the [[first past the post]] system of election.

Anyaa Sowutuom is one the constituencies that broke away from the now defunct [[Weija (Ghana parliament constituency)|Weija Constituency]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://citifmonline.com/2016/10/03/weija-residents-wont-be-swayed-by-ndcs-mere-promises-tina-mensah/|title=Weija residents won’t be swayed by NDC’s ‘mere’ promises – Tina Mensah|last=Ansah|first=Marian Efe|date=2016-10-03|website=Ghana News|access-date=2017-02-05}}</ref> Anyaa Sowutuom is located in the [[Greater Accra Region]] of [[Ghana]]. The current Member of Parliament is [[Shirley Ayorkor Botchway]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ghanaelections.peacefmonline.com/pages/2012/greateraccra/305/|title=Ghana Election 2012 Results - Anyaa Sowutuom Constituency|last=FM|first=Peace|website=Ghana Elections - Peace FM|access-date=2017-02-05}}</ref>

