'''Aramco Financial Services Company (AFSC)''' is a wholly owned subsidiary of [[Saudi Refining]], Inc., and ultimately of [[Aramco Services Company]].<ref>"[http://www.saudiaramco.com/irj/portal/anonymous?favlnk=%2FSaudiAramcoPublic%2Fdocs%2FOur+Business%2FInt%27l+Operations%2FSubsidiaries&ln=en Subsidiaries] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140226135426/http://www.saudiaramco.com/irj/portal/anonymous?favlnk=%2FSaudiAramcoPublic%2Fdocs%2FOur+Business%2FInt%27l+Operations%2FSubsidiaries&ln=en |date=February 26, 2014 }}." [[Saudi Aramco]]. Retrieved on January 19, 2011.</ref>

AFSC serves as the financial guarantor for the [[Certificate of Financial Responsibility|Certificates of Financial Responsibility]] issued by the [[U.S. Coast Guard]] to the tanker fleet owned and operated by [[Vela International Marine]], Ltd. This service guarantees the financial liability obligations of the Vela fleet under the [[Oil Pollution Act of 1990]], and ensures the ability of Vela-owned tankers to deliver [[Petroleum|crude]] shipments to U.S. ports.

