[[File:Unofficial flag of Vendsyssel.svg|thumb|right|Flag of [[Vendsyssel]]]]
[[File:Vendelbrog - Loenstrup 2015 ubt-001.JPG|thumb|Vendelbrog in [[Lønstrup]], 2015]]
[[File:Vendelbrog - Ringvejen 2009 ubt.jpg|thumb|Vendelbrog in [[Hjørring]], 2009]]
The proposed '''flag of [[Vendsyssel]]''' in [[Denmark]] was introduced by the mayor of [[Hjørring]] in 1976, and is used to some extent.

The flag is named '''Vendelbrog''' (with reference to the Danish flag [[Flag of Denmark|Dannebrog]] interpreted as '''The Danish cloth''').

== Design ==
It is a [[Nordic Cross Flag|Nordic Cross flag]] in blue, orange and green. The blue colour symbolizes the sea. The orange/red colour is symbol of the sun and the beaches of [[Vendsyssel]], and the green is for the lush nature. By tradition, only people '''born''' in [[Vendsyssel]] can use the flag.

The flag is not officially recognised, but it used to be a part of the insignia of the [[Royal Danish Air Force]] 723rd Air Squadron.<ref>[http://www.f-16.net/units_article281.html Royal Danish Air Force 723rd Air Squadron]</ref>

