{{multiple issues| {{notability|date=July 2014}} {{COI|date=July 2014}} }} The '''Malta Boxing Commission''' is an officially recognised professional boxing sanctioning organisation in [[Malta]]. Founded in 2011 by Alex Zammit and Gianluca DiCaro, the Malta Boxing Commission was inducted into the European Boxing Union at the 2011 AGM in Dublin, Ireland, but later had its membership revoked.<ref>{{cite web | last = Malta Independent | title = Pro Boxing Comes to Malta as EBU inducts Malta Boxing Commission | url = http://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2011-07-01/others/pro-boxing-comes-to-maltaas-ebu-inducts-malta-boxing-commission-294881 | accessdate = 1 July 2011}}</ref> In December 2012, former two-time, two-division champion of the world [[Steve Collins]] became the new President of the Malta Boxing Commission.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/steve-collins-joins-malta-boxing-commission--60043|title=Steve Collins Joins The Malta Boxing Commission|publisher=}}</ref> In June 2014, Malta Boxing Commission was inducted by the [[Association of Boxing Commissions]]<ref>{{cite web | last = Fight Network | title = Association of Boxing Commission Induct Malta Commission | url = http://fightnetwork.com/news/48180:association-of-boxing-commission-induct-maltacommission/ | accessdate = 11 June 2014}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web | last = Association Of Boxing Commissioners | title = Boxing Commissioners Contact Information | url = http://abcboxing.com/International.html | accessdate = 11 June 2014}}</ref> In June 2014 the Malta Boxing Commission launched the MBC International Championship.<ref>{{cite web | last = Eastside Boxing | title = MBC Unveil New International Championship | url = http://www.eastsideboxing.com/2014/mbc-unveil-new-international-championship/ | accessdate = 18 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | last = Fight Network | title = Prince Outpoints Svacina to Secure MBC International Title | url = http://fightnetwork.com/news/49420:prince-outpoints-svacine-to-secure-mbc-international-title/ | accessdate = 3 August 2014}}</ref> By March 2015,Charlie Cardona was appointed chairman, with founding partner Gianluca Di Caro becoming managing director. The Malta Boxing Commission is a UK Limited Company with registered offices at West Lancashire Investment Centre, Whitemoss Business Park, Maple View, Skelmersdale, Wigan, Lancashire, WN8 9TG and San Paul il-bahar in Malta.<ref>{{cite web | last = Malta Boxing Commission | title = MBC Contact page | url = http://maltaboxingcommission.com/?page_id=30 | accessdate = 18 June 2014}}</ref>
